OL,3,CRetired Army colonel 'died after four-
OL,4,Chour ambulance delay outside hospital'
OL,6,FCol Codd arrived at the Royal Cornwall
OL,7,FHospital in Truro at 4.30pm but was
OL,8,Fnot admitted until 9.11pm because no
OL,9,Fbed was available inside ` despite an
OL,10,Fambulance handover target of just 15
OL,11,Fminutes.
OL,13,FAs he waited inside the ambulance, he
OL,14,Fwas brought into the hospital to be
OL,15,Ftriaged by a nurse at 5.47pm and then
OL,16,Fexamined by a consultant at 6.10pm.
OL,18,FAn X-ray was taken for a suspected
OL,19,Ffractured hip and at 8pm Col Codd was
OL,20,Freviewed by a junior doctor, who then
OL,21,Fordered a CT scan of his pelvic area.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/11
