OL,3,CRetired Army colonel 'died after four-
OL,4,Chour ambulance delay outside hospital'
OL,6,FAt 9.11pm, Col Codd was finally
OL,7,Fadmitted to the hospital and placed in
OL,8,Fthe "majors" area of the department.
OL,10,FAn hour later he was found on the
OL,11,Ffloor with breathing difficulties
OL,12,Fhaving suffered a cardiac arrest from
OL,13,Fwhich he could not be resuscitated.
OL,15,FA post-mortem examination found Col
OL,16,FCodd had suffered a fracture to the
OL,17,Fcup of his right femur and had
OL,18,Fdeveloped a rare rectus sheath
OL,19,Fhematoma from the earlier fall, which
OL,20,Fwas the cause of his death.
